FT  10 MAR 92 / UK Company News: Operating officer for Young Group
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Young Group, the opencast and drift coal miner, yesterday announced the
appointment to its board, with immediate effect, of Mr Brian Calver, a
mining engineer with extensive experience at board level with RTZ mining
subsiduaries.
Mr Calver has joined the USM-quoted company as chief operating officer, a
new post designed to strengthen Young's management team. He will report
directly to chairman and chief executive Mr Bob Young and is expected to
become a director.
Young Group, which last week announced it was facing reduced 1991 profits
and needed more working capital, is currently negotiating with its bankers
and major shareholders for additional finance.
The creation of the new post, intended to allow Mr Bob Young, the company's
founder, to concentrate on broader strategic issues, had been planned well
before the group's need for more working capital became public knowledge.
