<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 92 / Unified companies register announced
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER MARSH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A COMPANY REGISTER which should help to improve the quality of the
government's economic statistics was announced yesterday by the Treasury.
The Pounds 4.3m system will be financed by the Central Statistical Office
and the Department of Employment, and should be ready next year. It will
replace the two separate registers now held by the departments.
The new business register will hold details about companies on computer,
including the nature of their businesses and their annual sales figures. The
information will help production of statistical surveys.
Although a Commons committee suggested the creation of a single register 26
years ago, the two systems have continued separately. Discrepancies between
the two registers are thought sometimes to lead to errors in official data.
The CSO says the new register offers the prospect of a reduced burden on
businesses. Theoretically, at least, fewer companies should have to provide
information on sales and other matters.
</TEXT>
