FT  09 MAR 92 / Observer: On the turntable
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
How time flies. Remember a punk band from the late 1970s called the Sex
Pistols? Didn't EMI sign up the group and then drop them after the group had
released only one record because it was worried about the bad publicity? And
didn't Richard Branson's Virgin records then release their album, Never Mind
the Bollocks, Here's the Sex Pistols, which contained a track called EMI?
It was not a flattering little ditty and ended with a loud raspberry.
Presumably, Thorn EMI now owns the rights to the company song.
