FT  09 MAR 92 / Warning over 'underclass'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PERSISTENT long-term unemployment presents the risk of a permanent
'underclass' developing in Britain and imposing serious strains on social,
political and civil order, a Policy Studies Institute report warns today.
The future of the underclass, says the report, depends mainly on the future
of employment. To prevent a permanent underclass forming there must be
effective policies for reducing and changing the distribution of
unemployment, or a change in the social structure so that employment was no
longer the source of money and everything else that society regarded as
valuable.
