 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
1970              17.5      4.7       8.7        4.5       na
1975              21.9      4.7      10.2        5.5       na
1980              21.2      2.4      11.7        5.8       na
1985              20.8      1.8      14.0        6.0       na
1987              20.4      1.7      13.3        6.1       4.9
1988              19.6      1.3      12.2        na       na
1989              19.4      1.8      11.9        na       na
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes: All figures refer to general government finance. First tier
(overview); The primary balance is the overall balance (revenue minus
expenditure) less net interest payments on public debt. Second tier
(revenue); Direct taxation (on incomes, profits and capital gains), is
here split into personal and corporate. Indirect taxation is mostly
that on expenditure, either general (eg VAT) or specific (eg customs
duties). Also includes taxes on vehicles. Third tier (expenditure);
government purchases of goods and services for consumption and for
investment (gross fixed capital formation). The expenditure breakdown
excludes debt interest payments, subsidies, and capital transfers.
Health and Education figures include current and capital expenditure.
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: OECD.
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
